HEADWORD: Goose-rumped
<hw>Goose"-rumped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the tail set low and buttocks that fall away sharply from
the croup; -- said of certain horses.</def>⟦br⟧
